# Active chain IDs for the current rehearsal cycle.

#

# The export script (`exportFrontendDeployments.sh`) filters the

# consolidated `deployments.json` by this list:

#

# - Per-chain folders whose chainId is listed → included in the

# consolidated `deployments.json` and crawled by the hf-watcher.

# - Folders for retired chains stay on disk for forensic value

# (audit trail of what was deployed when) but stop being

# crawled and stop appearing in the frontend's chain picker.

#

# To retire a chain: remove its line from this file, run

# `bash contracts/script/exportFrontendDeployments.sh`, redeploy

# the watcher with `cd ops/hf-watcher && npx wrangler deploy`, then

# purge stale rows with

# `FORCE=1 bash ops/hf-watcher/scripts/purge-chain.sh <chainId>`.

#

# Format: one chainId per line, integer; `#` starts a comment;

# blank lines ignored. The allow-list is intentionally explicit —

# adding a new chain folder to disk does NOT auto-include it.

#

# Phase 1 testnet trio (Base canonical, Arb + OP mirrors). Diamond

# addresses are NOT listed here — the canonical source is each chain's

# `contracts/deployments/<slug>/addresses.json`, auto-rewritten by

# `deploy-chain.sh` on every redeploy. Duplicating addresses here was

# drift-prone (stale after every fresh redeploy).

# 31337 # anvil (local devnet) — commented for the testnet cut; its local
#         addresses.json is stale (chain wiped). Re-add after a fresh
#         `anvil-bootstrap.sh` if you want the local diamond in the bundle.
